==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[corsaire]], from mediaeval Latin [[cursarius]], from [[cursa]], [[cursus]] ‘plunder’, a specialised sense of Latin [[cursus]] ‘course’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈkɔ:sɛ:/}}
*{{audio|en-us-corsair.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[privateersman]] or [[pirate]] in the Mediterranean, especially along the [[Barbary coast]]
# A pirate [[ship]] or [[privateer]].
# A nocturnal [[bug]] of the genus ''Rasahus'', found in the southern US.


